---
const { skill } = Astro.props;
---
<div class="v-research">
  <p class="rs-path">.scratch/findings-content-collections.md</p>
  <h3 class="rs-title">Findings: Astro content collections</h3>
  <p class="rs-intent">Can we type Markdown skill entries and query them at build time? Yes — via <code>defineCollection</code> + Zod.</p>
  <ul class="rs-claims">
    <li>Collections live under <code>src/content/</code>; each folder becomes a queryable set with a Zod schema enforced at build.<sup>[1]</sup></li>
    <li><code>getCollection('skills')</code> returns typed entries; invalid frontmatter fails the build rather than shipping broken pages.<sup>[1]</sup></li>
    <li>The <code>render()</code> helper compiles an entry's body to a component, so MDX and plain Markdown share one pipeline.<sup>[2]</sup></li>
  </ul>
  <div class="rs-sources">
    <p class="rs-sources-h">Sources</p>
    <ol>
      <li><span class="rs-num">[1]</span> docs.astro.build — Content Collections <span class="rs-url">/en/guides/content-collections/</span></li>
      <li><span class="rs-num">[2]</span> docs.astro.build — Rendering entries <span class="rs-url">/en/reference/modules/astro-content/#render</span></li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .v-research {
    padding: 28px 30px; background: #fffefb; border: 1px solid #e7e3d8;
    border-radius: 8px; color: #17150f; font-family: var(--font-serif);
    box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,.03);
  }
  .rs-path {
    margin: 0 0 14px; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11.5px;
    color: #8f897b; letter-spacing: .01em;
  }
  .rs-title { margin: 0 0 6px; font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -.01em; }
  .rs-intent { margin: 0 0 18px; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.5; color: #5b564a; }
  .rs-intent code, .rs-claims code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .85em; background: #f4f1ea;
    padding: 1px 5px; border-radius: 4px; color: #8a4527;
  }
  .rs-claims { margin: 0 0 20px; padding-left: 20px; }
  .rs-claims li { margin-bottom: 11px; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.55; color: #2b281f; }
  .rs-claims sup { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; color: #b4552d; margin-left: 2px; }
  .rs-sources { border-top: 1px solid #ece7db; padding-top: 14px; }
  .rs-sources-h {
    margin: 0 0 8px; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px;
    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .08em; color: #8f897b;
  }
  .rs-sources ol { margin: 0; padding: 0; list-style: none; }
  .rs-sources li { font-size: 13px; color: #5b564a; margin-bottom: 5px; }
  .rs-num { font-family: var(--font-mono); color: #b4552d; margin-right: 6px; }
  .rs-url { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11.5px; color: #a19a89; }
</style>
